name: Dark Side of the Moon
description: Homage to the LP Dark Side of the Moon by Pink Floyd, released in 1973. The cover was created by  Storm Thorgerson, following keyboardist Richard Wrightâ€™s suggestion for a classy, bold design. My older brother was a huge Pink Floyd fan so I was always intrigued by their music. I would sneak into his bedroom, a strict no-Jon zone, to dub his collection on to tape. I fell in love with this album. Listening to it now is like bathing in a vat of warm tea.
